   "source": [
    "# Project 12 — Production AI Platform\n",
    "\n",
    "## Overview\n",
    "This final project ties together everything from projects 7–11 into a **production-ready AI microservices platform**. We build four services that work together:\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "Client → API Gateway → RAG Service → LLM Service → Eval Service\n",
    "              ↓\n",
    "         [Cache] [Rate Limiter] [Cost Tracker] [Monitoring]\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "**Services:**\n",
    "- `gateway.py` — API gateway with auth, rate limiting, semantic caching, cost tracking\n",
    "- `rag_service.py` — document ingestion and retrieval\n",
    "- `llm_service.py` — LLM inference with retry logic\n",
    "- `eval_service.py` — LLM output evaluation"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "l1000002",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Theory — Production AI Systems\n",
    "\n",
    "### Microservices Architecture\n",
    "Breaking a system into small, independent services that communicate over APIs:\n",
    "- **Scalability**: scale individual services independently\n",
    "- **Isolation**: failures in one service don't cascade\n",
    "- **Deployability**: update individual services without downtime\n",
    "\n",
    "### API Gateway Pattern\n",
    "A single entry point that handles cross-cutting concerns:\n",
    "- Authentication\n",
    "- Rate limiting\n",
    "- Load balancing\n",
    "- Request routing\n",
    "- Response caching\n",
    "\n",
    "### Semantic Caching\n",
    "Cache LLM responses not just on exact query match, but on **semantic similarity**:\n",
    "$$\\text{cache\_hit} = \\begin{cases} \\text{True} & \\text{if } \\text{cosim}(\\mathbf{q}_{new}, \\mathbf{q}_{cached}) > \\theta \\\\ \\text{False} & \\text{otherwise} \\end{cases}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "For LLMs, a cache hit saves significant cost. Threshold $\\theta \\approx 0.92$ works well in practice.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Token Bucket Rate Limiting\n",
    "Tokens accumulate at a fixed rate $r$ up to capacity $C$. Each request costs $c$ tokens:\n",
    "$$\\text{tokens}(t) = \\min(C, \\text{tokens}(t_0) + r \\cdot (t - t_0))$$\n",
    "\n",
    "If $\\text{tokens}(t) < c$: **reject** request with 429. Otherwise: **accept** and deduct $c$.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Circuit Breaker\n",
    "Prevents cascading failures by temporarily blocking calls to a failing service:\n",
    "```\n",
    "CLOSED → (too many failures) → OPEN → (timeout) → HALF-OPEN → (success) → CLOSED\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "### Observability — Logs, Metrics, Traces\n",
    "- **Logs**: structured events with timestamp, level, context\n",
    "- **Metrics**: numeric time-series (latency, throughput, errors)\n",
    "- **Traces**: end-to-end request flow across services (distributed tracing)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "l1000003",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
